        "Could you create a '**view**' method and a '**get_query**' method?\r\n\r\nThe '**view**' method would be akin to a standard RDBMS read-only view.\r\n\r\nThe '**get_query**' method could be used as a means to save frequently used queries that modify data.\r\n\r\nExamples for the '**view**' command:\r\n\r\n```\r\nr.create_view(\"my-view\", r.table('my-table').pluck('my-field-1', 'my-field-2').limit(200)).run(conn)\r\n\r\n(somewhere else, later on...)\r\n\r\nr.view('my-view').pluck('my-field-2').limit(100).run(conn)\r\n```\r\n"
